{
  "diffMode": "binary",
  "formatName": "HDF4 Scientific Data",
  "version": "1.0",
  "extensions": [".hdf", ".h4", ".hdf4"],
  "description": "HDF4 (Hierarchical Data Format version 4) — scientific multi-object data format from NCSA. Magic: 0E 03 13 01 (4 bytes at offset 0). HDF4 uses tagged data elements (Data Descriptors — DDs). Each DD: tag(2B BE) + ref(2B BE) + offset(4B BE) + length(4B BE). Key tags: 0x001E=SciData (scientific dataset), 0x0706=Vgroup (group/hierarchy node), 0x0702=Vdata (table structure), 0x0301=RIG (raster image group), 0x022B=DFTAG_SDG (scientific data group). Attribute tag: 0x00AA. HDF4 is superseded by HDF5 but remains in active use for legacy NASA EOS products: MODIS (Terra/Aqua), ASTER, MISR Level 1-2 data products distributed by NASA LAADS DAAC and LP DAAC.",
  "category": "Science",
  "author": "WPFHexaEditor Team",
  "preferredEditor": "hex-editor",
  "references": {
    "specifications": [
      "HDF4 File Format Specification — NCSA/The HDF Group",
      "NASA EOSDIS Data Format Specification for HDF4",
      "HDF4 Reference Manual — The HDF Group"
    ],
    "WebLinks": [
      "https://www.hdfgroup.org/solutions/hdf4/",
      "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hierarchical_Data_Format",
      "https://lpdaac.usgs.gov/data/get-started-data/collection-overview/missions/modis-overview/"
    ]
  },
  "detection": {
    "signatures": [
      {
        "value": "0E031301",
        "offset": 0,
        "label": "HDF4 magic — Hierarchical Data Format version 4 at offset 0",
        "weight": 1.0
      }
    ],
    "matchMode": "any",
    "MinimumScore": 0.9,
    "required": true,
    "Strength": "Strong",
    "EntropyHint": { "min": 4.0, "max": 7.8 },
    "validation": {
      "minFileSize": 12,
      "maxSignatureOffset": 0,
      "note": "HDF4 always starts with 0E 03 13 01. HDF5 uses a different magic (89 48 44 46 0D 0A 1A 0A). Never confuse the two — see HDF5.whfmt."
    }
  },
  "variables": {
    "hdf4Magic": "",
    "firstTag": 0,
    "firstRef": 0,
    "firstOffset": 0,
    "firstLength": 0
  },
  "blocks": [
    {
      "type": "signature",
      "name": "HDF4 Magic",
      "offset": 0,
      "length": 4,
      "color": "#FF6B6B",
      "opacity": 0.45,
      "description": "HDF4 magic bytes 0x0E 0x03 0x13 0x01 at offset 0 (4 bytes). This 4-byte sequence uniquely identifies Hierarchical Data Format version 4 as defined by NCSA (now The HDF Group). HDF4 uses a linked-list structure of Data Descriptors (DDs) to organize tagged data elements. Each element has a tag identifying its type and a reference number. All multi-byte integers in HDF4 are big-endian.",
      "storeAs": "hdf4Magic",
      "valueType": "hex"
    },
    {
      "type": "field",
      "name": "First DD Tag",
      "offset": 4,
      "length": 2,
      "color": "#4ECDC4",
      "opacity": 0.35,
      "description": "Tag number of the first Data Descriptor (DD) at offset 4 (2 bytes, big-endian uint16). The tag identifies the type of data element. Standard tags: 0x001E=SciData (numeric array), 0x0706=Vgroup (named group), 0x0702=Vdata (table), 0x0301=RIG (raster image group), 0x022B=SDG (scientific data group), 0x00AA=attribute. Special tag 0x0002 = Data Descriptor Block (DDB), which contains the initial array of DDs.",
      "storeAs": "firstTag",
      "valueType": "uint16",
      "endianness": "big",
      "valueMap": {
        "2": "Data Descriptor Block (DDB)",
        "30": "SciData — scientific dataset array",
        "170": "Attribute data element",
        "555": "Scientific Data Group (SDG)",
        "769": "Raster Image Group (RIG)",
        "1794": "Vdata — table structure",
        "1798": "Vgroup — named group"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "field",
      "name": "First DD Reference",
      "offset": 6,
      "length": 2,
      "color": "#95E1D3",
      "opacity": 0.35,
      "description": "Reference number of the first Data Descriptor at offset 6 (2 bytes, big-endian uint16). Together with the tag, the (tag, ref) pair uniquely identifies a data element within the HDF4 file. Reference numbers are assigned sequentially during file creation. Reference number 1 typically identifies the first created data element. The DDL (Data Descriptor List) is a linked list of blocks, each containing up to ~16 DDs.",
      "storeAs": "firstRef",
      "valueType": "uint16",
      "endianness": "big"
    },
    {
      "type": "field",
      "name": "First DD Data Offset",
      "offset": 8,
      "length": 4,
      "color": "#FFE66D",
      "opacity": 0.35,
      "description": "Byte offset of the first data element's data within the HDF4 file at offset 8 (4 bytes, big-endian uint32). This offset points to the raw data payload for the tagged element. For the initial Data Descriptor Block (DDB), this offset points to the array of subsequent Data Descriptors that form the file's object catalog. Must be >= 4 (after the file magic).",
      "storeAs": "firstOffset",
      "valueType": "uint32",
      "endianness": "big"
    },
    {
      "type": "field",
      "name": "First DD Data Length",
      "offset": 12,
      "length": 4,
      "color": "#A8E6CF",
      "opacity": 0.35,
      "description": "Byte length of the first data element's payload at offset 12 (4 bytes, big-endian uint32). For the initial DDB (Data Descriptor Block), this is the size of the DD array that follows. Each DD is 12 bytes: tag(2B) + ref(2B) + offset(4B) + length(4B). The DDB contains the file-level index of all named data elements. Must be > 0 for a non-empty file.",
      "storeAs": "firstLength",
      "valueType": "uint32",
      "endianness": "big"
    },
    {
      "type": "metadata",
      "name": "HDF4 Magic",
      "variable": "hdf4Magic",
      "description": "0E031301 — HDF4 file magic bytes"
    },
    {
      "type": "metadata",
      "name": "First DD Tag",
      "variable": "firstTag",
      "description": "Tag type of first Data Descriptor"
    },
    {
      "type": "metadata",
      "name": "First DD Reference",
      "variable": "firstRef",
      "description": "Reference number of first Data Descriptor"
    },
    {
      "type": "metadata",
      "name": "First DD Offset",
      "variable": "firstOffset",
      "description": "Byte offset of first element data in file"
    }
  ],
  "assertions": [
    {
      "name": "HDF4 magic valid",
      "expression": "hdf4Magic == '0E031301'",
      "severity": "error",
      "message": "HDF4 file must start with 0E 03 13 01 — not a valid HDF4 file"
    },
    {
      "name": "First offset valid",
      "expression": "firstOffset >= 4",
      "severity": "error",
      "message": "HDF4 first DD offset must be >= 4 (after magic)"
    },
    {
      "name": "First length positive",
      "expression": "firstLength > 0",
      "severity": "warning",
      "message": "HDF4 first DD length should be > 0 for a non-empty file"
    }
  ],
  "navigation": {
    "bookmarks": [
      { "name": "HDF4 Magic", "offset": 0, "icon": "\uE71B", "color": "#FF6B6B" },
      { "name": "First Data Descriptor", "offset": 4, "icon": "\uE8A5", "color": "#4ECDC4" }
    ]
  },
  "inspector": {
    "badge": "firstTag",
    "primaryField": "hdf4Magic",
    "showQualityScore": true,
    "groups": [
      {
        "title": "HDF4 Header",
        "icon": "\uE71B",
        "fields": ["hdf4Magic", "firstTag", "firstRef", "firstOffset", "firstLength"]
      }
    ]
  },
  "exportTemplates": [
    {
      "name": "HDF4 Header (JSON)",
      "format": "json",
      "fields": ["hdf4Magic", "firstTag", "firstRef", "firstOffset", "firstLength"]
    },
    {
      "name": "HDF4 DD Summary (Text)",
      "format": "text",
      "fields": ["hdf4Magic", "firstTag", "firstRef", "firstOffset"]
    }
  ],
  "forensic": {
    "category": "science-data",
    "riskLevel": "low",
    "suspiciousPatterns": [
      "Overlapping DD offsets indicate file corruption or malicious tampering",
      "Unusually large firstLength values may indicate truncated or incomplete write"
    ]
  },
  "aiHints": {
    "analysisContext": "HDF4 structure: magic(4B: 0E031301) + first DD(tag 2B BE + ref 2B BE + offset 4B BE + len 4B BE) = 12 bytes minimum header. DDB (tag=0x0002) contains linked list of DD arrays. Each DD array: ndds(2B BE, count) + next_block_offset(4B BE, 0=last) + ndds*(12B DD entries). SDS (Scientific Data Set) requires: DFTAG_SDG or DFTAG_NDG grouping tag + DFTAG_SDD (dimensions) + DFTAG_SD (data). All big-endian. Max 65535 tags per HDF4 file. NASA MODIS HDF4 files contain EOS metadata in HDFEOS_INFORMATION group.",
    "suggestedInspections": [
      "Bytes 0-3: magic 0E 03 13 01 — confirms HDF4 (not HDF5 which uses 89 48 44 46)",
      "Bytes 4-5 (uint16 BE): first DD tag — 0x0002=DDB, identifies file catalog block",
      "Bytes 8-11 (uint32 BE): first DD offset — location of Data Descriptor Block data",
      "Bytes 12-15 (uint32 BE): first DD length — size of initial DD catalog block"
    ]
  },
  "software": [
    "HDFView (The HDF Group viewer)",
    "pyhdf (Python HDF4 library)",
    "MATLAB (HDF4 reading via hdfread)",
    "NASA HEG (HDF-EOS to GeoTIFF Conversion Tool)",
    "GDAL (HDF4 driver for MODIS/ASTER products)",
    "IDL/ENVI (Exelis Visual Information Solutions)"
  ],
  "formatRelationships": {
    "category": "Science",
    "extensions": [".hdf", ".h4", ".hdf4"],
    "relatedFormats": ["HDF5", "NETCDF", "FITS"],
    "note": "HDF4 is the legacy predecessor of HDF5. Not architecturally compatible — different magic, structure, and APIs. NASA MODIS and ASTER products use HDF4 (HDF-EOS2). Newer NASA products (Sentinel, VIIRS) use HDF5 (HDF-EOS5). MINC1 neuroimaging format is built on NetCDF, not HDF4."
  },
  "MimeTypes": [
    "application/x-hdf"
  ],
  "UseCases": [
    "NASA MODIS satellite data products (MOD09, MYD11, etc.)",
    "NASA ASTER Level 1-2 surface reflectance products",
    "NASA MISR (Multi-angle Imaging SpectroRadiometer) data",
    "Legacy scientific computing array storage",
    "HDF-EOS2 data from Terra and Aqua satellites"
  ],
  "QualityMetrics": {
    "CompletenessScore": 90,
    "DocumentationLevel": "detailed",
    "BlocksDefined": 9,
    "ValidationRules": 3,
    "LastUpdated": "2026-04-15",
    "PriorityFormat": false,
    "AutoRefined": false
  },
  "TechnicalDetails": {
    "Format": "Tagged binary data with linked DD (Data Descriptor) catalog",
    "Magic": "0E 03 13 01 at offset 0",
    "Standard": "HDF4 File Format Specification — NCSA/The HDF Group",
    "Endianness": "big-endian for all header and descriptor fields",
    "MaxElements": "65,535 unique (tag, ref) pairs per file"
  }
}
